File: Telkom flagged earlier in November that it anticipated its profit to drop up to 40 percent. JOHANNESBURG - South African telecoms company Telkom SA has served unions with letters regarding planned job cuts, a company spokesperson said on Wednesday. "Out of respect for our employees, we will share information once we have engaged further with our employees and unions," Mooketsi Mocumi said in a WhatsApp response to questions. READ: Cell C drops Telkom The company has served unions with section 189 notices. At least 3,000 Telkom employees will be affected. Additional reporting eNCA